I found this app to be a useful tool for showing me different strategies in paying off debt, even giving me a debt free date. What it doesn't take into consideration is your income, therefore, can't show your income debt ratio, so the strategic planning is somewhat useless when you don't make enough money to follow the guide it sets up for you to accomplish a pay off point to become debt free. So if it included more detail, in other words, asked for more personal information it would make this app much better. If it was keeping your personal information and security in mind then it did great, however, to be a better debt pay off planner, I would think the app would have to get personal to provide a strategy the user can actually concider in achieving debt free status. A paid version with these features would be my recommendation. I would pay a couple bucks for an app to help me become debt free, definitely cheaper than a financial advisor, which your bank usually offers at no cost except for the driving to the bank part. I paid 99¢ to get the info I received in this version, although unable to use its suggested strategy, I get what it takes to achieve being debt free, I'd have to do my own calculations, much rather pay for more detailed app to provide me with the calculations. For what I paid, I'll say it's worth what info it can provide for you without any personal information being given. If You're In Debt, Try It!
